https://www.justonecookbook.com/gyudon/

1 small onion (thinly sliced)
1 green onioin cut however jhust dont julienne
.5 lb sukiyaki/thinly sliced beef
1.2 cup dashi
2 tbsp sake
2 tbsp mirin
3 tbsp light soy sauce 
1 tbsp sugar

cut beef into 3 inch wide pieces
in pot/wok add the dashi, sake, mirin, soy sauce, and sugar. (heat off)
spread onion in a layer in the pot/wok
spread beef on top of the onion
cover with lid, turn heat to medium.

skim scum when meat is browned, when boiling turn to simmer and cook for 3-5 minutes. It should cook real fast.

add scallions, lid back on for a minute.

congrats, youre done. really easy recipe.
